data.description:
You'll fall in love with this 3* Bedroom + 1.5 Bath Charming Corner Cottage on a Double Lot in historic Shelbyville!!

From the moment you step inside onto the beautiful hardwood floors, you'll be enamoured. Beyond that, you'll be impressed with how well cared for it has been by this owner. And psst! This home just has a great vibe that you can't help but notice!

Just inside the front door, you'll find a welcoming arched entryway that features a custom coat and hat rack and a perfect spot for an entry table. The living room hosts a wood-burning fireplace with a craftsman mantle and a custom accent wall. (Chimney has recently been inspected, cleaned and serviced for you.) Sit and listen to the fire crackle at the end of a long day or mount your TV above it and post up for your favorite series. Off the living room is a sizable dining area and modernized kitchen with custom cabinets, beautiful tile, top of the line stainless steel appliances (including new dishwasher) and granite countertops. The first floor offers a nice-sized bedroom and enchanting half bath. The upstairs has two bedrooms with plenty of closet space and a stylishly designed full bathroom. The newly reimagined downstairs has just been completely updated! Use this space as a fourth bedroom, game room or entertainment room-so many possibilities!. There's a large closet you can customize to your liking plus room to add a full-size bathroom. You'll also find the laundry room + plenty of storage downstairs. 

And that's just the beginning! The outside is an absolute oasis! The back patio boasts a state of the art built-in Jenn-Air grill and granite bar and dining area. There's more than enough space for gatherings or celebrations. Sit and sip a while under the stars and string lights. (Yes, the lights stay!) There's even a stacked stone outdoor wood burning fireplace.  Adjacent to the patio is the oversized driveway with new basketball goal + carport complete with security lighting + a shed for storing your lawn mower and tools. All this and the huge backyard + $5000 worth of landscaping upgrades around the entire property.

Seller is even offering a Home Warranty!

What a great opportunity to live in a home with historic charm and modern updates on a double lot on one of Shelbyville's favorite streets! Call today for your appointment!
